  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Public Relations Officer (PRO)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Roles and Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Liaise with stakeholders and various Statutory Boards, Government Departments in the form of emails, letters, phone calls and face to face meet up.</li><li>Conduct proper public relations works to engage and seek permission from JTC stakeholders for site occupation and site entry for the proposed work.</li><li>Notifying stakeholders and coordinating for pre-construction surveys and inspections.</li><li>Handle verbal/written and record feedbacks from public and stakeholders, subsequently follow up on the feedback until case closure.</li><li>Maintains proper record of all public relation cases, correspondences and communication materials.</li><li>Proactively initiate and take charge all public relations engagement and outreach activities</li><li>Prepare weekly management minutes and monthly report.</li><li>Manning of 24-hour Project Hotline</li><li>Other ad hoc duties and site office administration work as per assigned.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Minimum 3 years working experience of Public Relation Officer</li><li>Minimum ‘O’ levels or equivalent</li><li>Good communication and strong interpersonal skills to interact effectively with customers and key stakeholders.</li><li>Able to join in short notice</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
